parameters:
Thief Nora: It's amazing! It's a really nice house, just
like Clea-san!

Clea: I'm not sure if it's like me, but it has a reminiscent
of the past... It feels calming.

Priestess Sophia: Now, let's celebrate as promised. I
brought a special wine for this occasion.

Mage Relm: Don't you just want to drink? Well, I think
celebrating is a good idea though.
Priestess Sophia: Alright, the wine has been distributed!
Priestess Sophia: To celebrate the defeat of the dragon!
Thief Nora: To celebrate Clea-san's promotion!
Mage Relm: F-for the sake of our friendship!

Mage Relm: W-what is it, look over here! Come on, Clea-san,
say something too!
Clea: Let's raise a toast to the reunion with our comrades.
Thief Nora: Listen up~ We can't find the captains.
Thief Nora: The previous hideout is completely empty... ugh.

Priestess Sophia: Oh my, it seems Nora-chan is having a
tough time too.

Priestess Sophia: I am also having a hard time with the
construction of the tavern. There have been various
obstacles, and Eleo-chan seems to be struggling as well.

Mage Relm: Me too! I can't get permission for any
investigations or research at all!

Mage Relm: I can't go on without drinking something like
this!

Priestess Sophia: Oh my, what a good drinker you are! Relm-
chan, you might have some talent for this.

Mage Relm: Hehe, I'm an adult, you know! I can handle this
kind of wine easily, no problem at all!

Thief Nora: Clea-san, are you okay? Are you feeling sick, by
any chance?

Clea: I don't have any goals. I've been living empty days
from the dragon subjugation until today.

Clea: But after reuniting with everyone, I can see what I
should do.
Clea: Please let me assist with everyone's dreams.

Thief Nora: I-Is it really okay?! With Clea-san here, it's
like having the strength of a hundred people!

Priestess Sophia: I have also felt my limits, so I would
like to ask for your help, too.
Mage Relm: H-How about we all act together?

Clea: It's decided then. Let's cooperate with each other for
the sake of each person's dream.
Mage Relm: Yes...! I will take care of things properly!

Priestess Sophia: If that's the case, let's have a toast
again! Let's celebrate the reunion of the party and have a
drink!
Clea: Yes, let's drink to our heart's content today.

Clea: I also came here after a long time. I've been staying
overnight at the convenient guild dormitory.
Thief Nora: It's such a waste for something so splendid!

Sophia the priestess: 'Let's have a good time... ufufu, I'm
happy today because there are many drinking companions.'

Mage Relm: Tonight, I'll drink until morning! Now, minstrel-
san, sing a song to lift my spirits!
Minstrel: Hahaha, I got caught up in something amazing, huh?

Mage Relm: It's because of you that it turned out like this!
Normally, I wouldn't willingly drink something that gives me
a headache!

Priestess Sophia: Ufufu, alcohol is a friend of humanity.
That pain is also a proof of friendship, a proof of love...
Mage Relm: Now, the wine has reached everyone!
Mage Relm: Can you understand the pain in my heart?!

Priestess Sophia: R-Relm-chan, you've had too much to
drink... Are you okay?
Mage Relm: Not at all! I'm not okay at all!
Mage Relm: Hic, but seriously, you're really tone-deaf!

Minstrel: I've been playing for a long time, but hahaha, it
seems like being tone-deaf is incurable, huh?

Mage Relm: First of all, you're calling me a hero! Please
give a proper introduction to this genius!
Mage Relm: I am the great genius of the Magic Academy, Relm!
Minstrel: I've forgotten my own name, you know.

Minstrel: It's a story from thousands of years ago, and
since I was never called a hero and had the opportunity to
introduce myself by my real name.

Thief Nora: Um, aren't you lonely...? Forgetting your own
name and not having anyone who knows you.

Minstrel: I wonder... when you live for a long time, you end
up forgetting many things.

Minstrel: For someone like me, all that remains is my duty,
not my own name, nor the names of my friends, nor even my
own emotions.

Minstrel: That's why I try to remember even a little by
listening to stories from people like you.

Mage Relm: Then please make sure to leave the story of this
genius for future generations! The great genius who never
wavers in her belief for the sake of the world!

Mage Relm: In that sense, the world owes me a debt, doesn't
it? Someday, somewhere, it will have to be repaid, or things
won't add up!

Minstrel: Hahaha, if it's okay to be tone-deaf, I'll
definitely turn all of you into a song.

Minstrel: As for the song title... hmm... hahaha, I'll think
of it when the timing is right for your grand adventure.
Minstrel: Well then, it's about time for me to go home.
Mage Relm: Please wait... I'll give this to you!

Mage Relm: These are the materials for the spellbooks we
collected during our journey.

Mage Relm: Instead of giving up on your dreams, please
continue to protect this.

Minstrel: I understand. I promise to continue protecting
this without fail.

Clea: I apologize for not being able to fulfill the promise
of making Relm's dream come true.

Mage Relm: ...It's not Clea-san's fault. Thank you for
stopping me back then.

Mage Relm: Even though I knew how dangerous it would be to
pursue my dream without meeting all of you and traveling
together...

Mage Relm: Honestly, I still feel regretful and it's
difficult for me to switch gears immediately.
Mage Relm: My dream was said to have no value or meaning.

Mage Relm: Clea-san and the others may not have understood
its value, but I know they believed it had meaning.

Mage Relm: Although my dream didn't come true, the time I
spent chasing it with Clea-san and the others...

Mage Relm: For me, those days were truly like a dream,
filled with joy.

Mage Relm: Hey, what's the matter!? Hugging me like that...
That's why, again, ugh...

Mage Relm: I tried so hard to endure it, ugh, uaaahhh! Ngh,
it's so frustrating, ugh, aaahhhh!
Clea: I'll be with you all day today...
Village Chief Arukee: I'm sorry for the suddenness.
Receptionist Piste: No, I'm fine, but...

Village Chief Arukee: I hold a grudge against the
Adventurer's Guild.

Village Chief Arukee: Clea is the daughter of my close
friend. She is risking her life to fulfill the requests.

Village Chief Arukee: If anything were to happen to her, I
wouldn't be able to face my close friend and his wife...

Receptionist Piste: The Adventurer's Guild, Ftera, doesn't
force its members to stay as members.

Receptionist Piste: There is only one thing I must protect,
and that is to never betray, lie, or run away.

Receptionist Piste: Clea-chan has not betrayed, lied, or run
away until today.
Receptionist Piste: She is with us by her own strong will.

Village Chief Arukee: I apologize for saying something rude
earlier. It's reassuring to have adults like you by my
side...

Village Chief Arukee: That's why Clea has been able to grow.
She's still an unreliable girl, but I'll continue to rely on
her from now on.

Receptionist Piste: I think it would be better to talk to
her directly, don't you?

Village Chief Arukee: C-Could you really do such an
embarrassing thing? Here is the specialty honey that you
wanted, take it!

Receptionist Piste: Hehe, understood. I will use this honey
carefully.

Thief Nora: Clea-san, by the way, do you remember the statue
we obtained at the auction?
Clea: Yes, you mean the statue of the Hero, right?

Thief Nora: Since we went through all the trouble, let's
display the statue on the second floor!
